
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Game {
  -id: String
  -players: List<Player>
  -deck: Deck
  -scoringTable: ScoringTable
}

class Player {
  -id: String
  -name: String
}

class Deck {
  -id: String
  -cards: List<Card>
}

class Card {
  -id: String
  -suit: Suit
  -rank: Integer
  +compare(other: Card): Comparison
}

enum Suit {
  DIAMONDS
  HEARTS
  SPADES
  CLUBS
}

enum Comparison {
  LOWER
  EQUAL
  HIGHER
}

class ScoringTable {
  -id: String
  -rounds: List<Round>
}

abstract class Round {
  -id: String
  -winningPlayers: List<Player>
  -points: Integer
}

class JackRound extends Round {
}

class SoloRound extends Round {
  -soloType: SoloType
  -soloPlayer: Player
}

class MandatorySoloRound extends SoloRound {
}

enum SoloType {
  TRUMP
  JACK
  QUEEN
}

Game "1" *-- "4" Player
Game "1" *-- "1" Deck
Game "1" *-- "1" ScoringTable
Deck "1" *-- "48" Card
ScoringTable "1" *-- "0..*" Round
Round <|-- JackRound
Round <|-- SoloRound
SoloRound <|-- MandatorySoloRound
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **Game** is composed of **4 Players**, a **Deck**, and a **ScoringTable**.
- **Deck** contains up to **48 Cards**.
- Each **Card** has a `compare` method that returns a **Comparison** (lower, equal, higher).
- **ScoringTable** holds a list of **Rounds**.
- **Round** is an abstract class with two subclasses:
  - **JackRound**
  - **SoloRound** (which can be further specialized into **MandatorySoloRound**)
- **SoloRound** has a **SoloType** (trump, jack, queen) and one **SoloPlayer**.

